{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"What I'd like you to do is, just really quickly,"},{"time":2000,"text":"is just, sort of, nod to the person on your right,"},{"time":5000,"text":"and then nod to the person on your left."},{"time":8000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":12000,"text":"Now, chances are that over the last winter,"},{"time":16000,"text":"if you had been a beehive, either you or one of the two people"},{"time":19000,"text":"you just nodded at would have died."},{"time":23000,"text":"Now, that's an awful lot of bees."},{"time":27000,"text":"And this is the second year in a row we have lost over 30 percent"},{"time":31000,"text":"of the colonies, or we estimate we've lost 30 percent of the colonies over the winter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35000,"text":"Now, that's a lot, a lot of bees, and that's really important."},{"time":41000,"text":"And most of those losses are because of things we know."},{"time":44000,"text":"We know that there are these varroa mites that have introduced"},{"time":47000,"text":"and caused a lot of losses, and we also have this new phenomenon,"},{"time":50000,"text":"which I talked about last year, Colony Collapse Disorder."},{"time":53000,"text":"And here we see a picture on top of a hill in Central Valley last December."},{"time":58000,"text":"And below, you can see all these out yards,"},{"time":60000,"text":"or temporary yards, where the colonies are brought in until February,"},{"time":65000,"text":"and then they're shipped out to the almonds."},{"time":68000,"text":"And one documentary writer, who was here and looked at this two months"},{"time":71000,"text":"after I was here, described this not as beehives"},{"time":74000,"text":"but as a graveyard, with these empty white boxes with no bees left in them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":80000,"text":"Now, I'm going to sum up a year's worth of work in two sentences"},{"time":84000,"text":"to say that we have been trying to figure out"},{"time":86000,"text":"what the cause of this is."},{"time":88000,"text":"And what we know is that it's as if the bees have caught a flu."},{"time":91000,"text":"And this flu has wiped through the population of bees."},{"time":96000,"text":"In some cases, and in fact in most cases in one year,"},{"time":100000,"text":"this flu was caused by a new virus to us,"},{"time":103000,"text":"or newly identified by us, called Israeli Acute Paralysis virus."},{"time":107000,"text":"It was called that because a guy in Israel first found it,"},{"time":109000,"text":"and he now regrets profoundly calling it that disease, because,"},{"time":113000,"text":"of course, there's the implication."},{"time":114000,"text":"But we think this virus is pretty ubiquitous."},{"time":117000,"text":"It's also pretty clear that the bees sometimes catch other viruses"},{"time":120000,"text":"or other flus, and so the question we're still struggling with,"},{"time":124000,"text":"and the question that keeps us up at night,"},{"time":126000,"text":"is why have the bees suddenly become so susceptible to this flu,"},{"time":131000,"text":"and why are they so susceptible to these other diseases?"},{"time":136000,"text":"And we don't have the answer to that yet,"},{"time":138000,"text":"and we spend a lot of time trying to figure that out."},{"time":141000,"text":"We think perhaps it's a combination of factors."},{"time":143000,"text":"We know from the work of a very large and dynamic working team"},{"time":147000,"text":"that, you know, we're finding a lot of different pesticides"},{"time":151000,"text":"in the hive, and surprisingly, sometimes the healthiest hives"},{"time":154000,"text":"have the most pesticides. And so we discover all these"},{"time":157000,"text":"very strange things that we can't begin to understand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161000,"text":"And so this opens up the whole idea of looking at colony health."},{"time":166000,"text":"Now of course, if you lose a lot of colonies,"},{"time":169000,"text":"beekeepers can replace them very quickly."},{"time":171000,"text":"And that's why we've been able to recover from a lot of loss."},{"time":174000,"text":"If we lost one in every three cows in the winter, you know,"},{"time":178000,"text":"the National Guard would be out."},{"time":179000,"text":"But what beekeepers can do is, if they have one surviving colony,"},{"time":183000,"text":"they can split that colony in two."},{"time":186000,"text":"And then the one half that doesn't have a queen, they can buy a queen."},{"time":189000,"text":"It comes in the mail; it can come from Australia or Hawaii or Florida,"},{"time":193000,"text":"and you can introduce that queen."},{"time":195000,"text":"And in fact, America was the first country"},{"time":197000,"text":"that ever did mail-delivery queens and in fact,"},{"time":200000,"text":"it's part of the postal code that you have to deliver queens by mail"},{"time":207000,"text":"in order to make sure that we have enough bees in this country."},{"time":212000,"text":"If you don't just want a queen, you can buy, actually,"},{"time":214000,"text":"a three-pound package of bees, which comes in the mail, and of course,"},{"time":218000,"text":"the Postal Office is always very concerned when they get,"},{"time":221000,"text":"you know, your three-pound packages of bees."},{"time":223000,"text":"And you can install this in your hive and replace that dead-out."},{"time":227000,"text":"So it means that beekeepers are very good at replacing dead-outs,"},{"time":231000,"text":"and so they've been able to cover those losses."},{"time":234000,"text":"So even though we've lost 30 percent of the colonies every year,"},{"time":237000,"text":"the same number of colonies have existed in the country,"},{"time":241000,"text":"at about 2.4 million colonies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244000,"text":"Now, those losses are tragic on many fronts,"},{"time":248000,"text":"and one of those fronts is for the beekeeper."},{"time":250000,"text":"And it's really important to talk about beekeepers first,"},{"time":253000,"text":"because beekeepers are among the most fascinating people you'll ever meet."},{"time":256000,"text":"If this was a group of beekeepers, you would have everyone"},{"time":259000,"text":"from the card-carrying NRA member who's, you know, live free or die,"},{"time":264000,"text":"to the, you know, the self-expressed quirky San Francisco"},{"time":267000,"text":"backyard pig farmer."},{"time":269000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":271000,"text":"And you get all of these people in the same room,"},{"time":274000,"text":"and they're all engaged and they're getting along,"},{"time":278000,"text":"and they're all there because of the passion for bees."},{"time":281000,"text":"Now, there's another part of that community"},{"time":283000,"text":"which are the commercial beekeepers,"},{"time":284000,"text":"the ones who make their livelihood from beekeeping alone."},{"time":287000,"text":"And these tend to be some of the most independent, tenacious,"},{"time":295000,"text":"intuitive, you know, inventive people you will ever meet."},{"time":299000,"text":"They're just fascinating. And they're like that all over the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":302000,"text":"I had the privilege of working in Haiti just for two weeks earlier this year."},{"time":306000,"text":"And Haiti, if you've ever been there, is just a tragedy."},{"time":309000,"text":"I mean, there may be 100 explanations"},{"time":311000,"text":"for why Haiti is the impoverished nation it is,"},{"time":314000,"text":"but there is no excuse to see that sort of squalor."},{"time":317000,"text":"But you meet this beekeeper, and I met this beekeeper here,"},{"time":320000,"text":"and he is one of the most knowledgeable beekeepers I've ever met."},{"time":322000,"text":"No formal education, but very knowledgeable."},{"time":324000,"text":"We needed beeswax for a project we were working on; he was so capable,"},{"time":329000,"text":"he was able to render the nicest block of beeswax I have ever seen"},{"time":333000,"text":"from cow dung, tin cans and his veil, which he used as a screening,"},{"time":338000,"text":"right in this meadow. And so that ingenuity is inspiring."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342000,"text":"We also have Dave Hackenberg, who is the poster child of CCD."},{"time":345000,"text":"He's the one who first identified this condition"},{"time":347000,"text":"and raised the alarm bells."},{"time":349000,"text":"And he has a history of these trucks,"},{"time":351000,"text":"and he's moved these bees up and down the coast."},{"time":354000,"text":"And a lot of people talk about trucks and moving bees,"},{"time":357000,"text":"and that being bad, but we've done that for thousands of years."},{"time":360000,"text":"The ancient Egyptians used to move bees up and down the Nile on rafts,"},{"time":363000,"text":"so this idea of a movable bee force is not new at all."},{"time":369000,"text":"And one of our real worries with Colony Collapse Disorder"},{"time":373000,"text":"is the fact that it costs so much money to replace those dead-out colonies."},{"time":377000,"text":"And you can do that one year in a row,"},{"time":380000,"text":"you may be able to do it two years in a row."},{"time":382000,"text":"But if you're losing 50 percent to 80 percent of your colonies,"},{"time":386000,"text":"you can't survive three years in a row. And we're really worried"},{"time":389000,"text":"about losing this segment of our industry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":393000,"text":"And that's important for many fronts,"},{"time":395000,"text":"and one of them is because of that culture that's in agriculture."},{"time":399000,"text":"And these migratory beekeepers are the last nomads of America."},{"time":404000,"text":"You know, they pick up their hives;"},{"time":405000,"text":"they move their families once or twice in a year."},{"time":408000,"text":"And if you look at Florida, in Dade City, Florida,"},{"time":411000,"text":"that's where all the Pennsylvania beekeepers go."},{"time":413000,"text":"And then 20 miles down the road is Groveland,"},{"time":415000,"text":"and that's where all the Wisconsin beekeepers go."},{"time":417000,"text":"And if you're ever in Central Valley in February, you go to this café"},{"time":422000,"text":"at 10 o'clock in the morning, Kathy and Kate's."},{"time":425000,"text":"And that's where all the beekeepers come after a night of moving bees"},{"time":428000,"text":"into the almond groves."},{"time":429000,"text":"They all have their breakfast"},{"time":430000,"text":"and complain about everyone right there. And it's a great experience,"},{"time":435000,"text":"and I really encourage you to drop in at that diner during that time,"},{"time":438000,"text":"because that's quite essential American experience."},{"time":441000,"text":"And we see these families, these nomadic families, you know,"},{"time":445000,"text":"father to son, father to son, and these guys are hurting."},{"time":449000,"text":"And they're not people who like to ask for help,"},{"time":452000,"text":"although they are the most helpful people ever."},{"time":454000,"text":"If there's one guy who loses all his bees because of a truck overhaul,"},{"time":458000,"text":"everyone pitches in and gives 20 hives"},{"time":460000,"text":"to help him replace those lost colonies."},{"time":462000,"text":"And so, it's a very dynamic, and I think,"},{"time":464000,"text":"historic and exciting community to be involved with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":471000,"text":"Of course, the real importance for bees is not the honey."},{"time":474000,"text":"And although I highly encourage you, all use honey."},{"time":476000,"text":"I mean, it's the most ethical sweetener,"},{"time":479000,"text":"and you know, it's a dynamic and fun sweetener."},{"time":482000,"text":"But we estimate that about one in three bites of food we eat"},{"time":486000,"text":"is directly or indirectly pollinated by honeybees."},{"time":491000,"text":"Now, I want to just illustrate that in the fact"},{"time":493000,"text":"that if we look at the breakfast I had yesterday morning --"},{"time":497000,"text":"a little cranberry juice, some fruits, some granola,"},{"time":500000,"text":"I should have had whole wheat bread, I realized, but you know,"},{"time":503000,"text":"jam on my Wonderbread, and some coffee --"},{"time":507000,"text":"and had we taken out all those ingredients,"},{"time":512000,"text":"-- except for the almonds I wasn't going to pick out from the granola --"},{"time":514000,"text":"if we had taken out all those ingredients"},{"time":517000,"text":"the bees had indirectly or directly pollinated,"},{"time":520000,"text":"we wouldn't have much on our plate."},{"time":522000,"text":"So if we did not have bees, it's not like we would starve,"},{"time":525000,"text":"but clearly our diet would be diminished."},{"time":530000,"text":"It's said that for bees, the flower is the fountain of life,"},{"time":533000,"text":"and for flowers bees are the messengers of love."}]},{"cues":[{"time":536000,"text":"And that's a really great expression, because really,"},{"time":539000,"text":"bees are the sex workers for flowers. They are, you know --"},{"time":542000,"text":"they get paid for their services."},{"time":544000,"text":"They get paid by pollen and nectar,"},{"time":546000,"text":"to move that male sperm, the pollen, from flower to flower."},{"time":550000,"text":"And there are flowers that are self-infertile. That means they can't --"},{"time":553000,"text":"the pollen in their bloom can't fertilize themselves."},{"time":557000,"text":"So in an apple orchard, for instance, you'll have rows of 10 apples"},{"time":560000,"text":"of one variety, and then you have another apple tree"},{"time":563000,"text":"that's a different type of pollen."},{"time":565000,"text":"And bees are very faithful."},{"time":566000,"text":"When they're out pollinating or gathering pollen from one flower,"},{"time":570000,"text":"they stay to that crop exclusively, in order to help generate."},{"time":574000,"text":"And of course, they're made to carry this pollen."},{"time":578000,"text":"They build up a static electric charge and the pollen jumps on them"},{"time":581000,"text":"and helps spread that pollen from bloom to bloom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585000,"text":"However, honeybees are a minority."},{"time":587000,"text":"Honeybees are not native to America; they were introduced"},{"time":590000,"text":"with the colonialists."},{"time":591000,"text":"And there are actually more species of bees"},{"time":594000,"text":"than there are mammals and birds combined."},{"time":596000,"text":"In Pennsylvania alone, we have been surveying bees for 150 years,"},{"time":601000,"text":"and very intensely in the last three years."},{"time":604000,"text":"We have identified over 400 species of bees in Pennsylvania."},{"time":609000,"text":"Thirty-two species have not been identified or found in the state since 1950."},{"time":615000,"text":"Now, that could be because we haven't been sampling right,"},{"time":618000,"text":"but it does, I think, suggest that something's wrong"},{"time":620000,"text":"with the pollinator force. And these bees are fascinating."}]},{"cues":[{"time":623000,"text":"We have bumblebees on the top."},{"time":625000,"text":"And bumblebees are what we call eusocial: they're not truly social,"},{"time":628000,"text":"because only the queen is, over winter."},{"time":631000,"text":"We also have the sweat bees, and these are little gems flying around."},{"time":634000,"text":"They're like tiny little flies and they fly around."},{"time":637000,"text":"And then you have another type of bee, which we call kleptoparasites,"},{"time":641000,"text":"which is a very fancy way of saying, bad-minded, murdering --"},{"time":649000,"text":"what's the word I'm looking for? Murdering --"},{"time":652000,"text":"Audience: Bee?"},{"time":653000,"text":"Dennis vanEngelsdorp: Bee. Okay, thanks."},{"time":654000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":656000,"text":"What these bees do is, they sit there. These solitary bees,"},{"time":663000,"text":"they drill a hole in the ground or drill a hole in a branch,"},{"time":666000,"text":"and they collect pollen and make it into a ball,"},{"time":668000,"text":"and they lay an egg on it."},{"time":670000,"text":"Well, these bees hang out at that hole,"},{"time":671000,"text":"and they wait for that mother to fly away, they go in, eat the egg,"},{"time":675000,"text":"and lay their own egg there. So they don't do any work."},{"time":678000,"text":"And so, in fact, if you know you have these kleptoparasitic bees,"},{"time":683000,"text":"you know that your environment is healthy,"},{"time":685000,"text":"because they're top-of-the-food-chain bees."},{"time":688000,"text":"And in fact, there is now a red list of pollinators"},{"time":692000,"text":"that we're worried have disappeared, and on top of that list"},{"time":696000,"text":"are a lot of these kleptoparasites, but also these bumblebees."},{"time":699000,"text":"And in fact, if you guys live on the West Coast,"},{"time":701000,"text":"go to these websites here, and they're really looking for people"},{"time":704000,"text":"to look for some of these bumblebees, because we think"},{"time":707000,"text":"some have gone extinct. Or some, the population has declined."}]},{"cues":[{"time":711000,"text":"And so it's not just honeybees that are in trouble,"},{"time":714000,"text":"but we don't understand these native pollinators"},{"time":717000,"text":"or all those other parts of our community."},{"time":720000,"text":"And of course, bees are not the only important factor here."},{"time":724000,"text":"There are other animals that pollinate, like bats,"},{"time":726000,"text":"and bats are in trouble too."},{"time":728000,"text":"And I'm glad I'm a bee man and not a bat man,"},{"time":730000,"text":"because there's no money to research the bat problems."},{"time":734000,"text":"And bats are dying at an extraordinary rate."},{"time":737000,"text":"White-nose syndrome has wiped out populations of bats."},{"time":740000,"text":"If there's a cave in New York that had 15,000 bats in it,"},{"time":745000,"text":"and there are 1,000 left. That's like San Francisco"},{"time":749000,"text":"becoming the population of half of this county in three years."},{"time":754000,"text":"And so that's incredible. And there's no money to do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":756000,"text":"But I'm glad to say that I think we know the cause"},{"time":758000,"text":"of all these conditions, and that cause is NDD:"},{"time":762000,"text":"Nature Deficit Disorder."},{"time":764000,"text":"And that is that I think that what we have in our society is,"},{"time":768000,"text":"we forgot our connection with nature."},{"time":770000,"text":"And I think if we reconnect to nature,"},{"time":773000,"text":"we'll be able to have the resources and that interest"},{"time":776000,"text":"to solve these problems."},{"time":778000,"text":"And I think that there is an easy cure for NDD."},{"time":781000,"text":"And that is, make meadows and not lawns."},{"time":785000,"text":"And I think we have lost our connection,"},{"time":787000,"text":"and this is a wonderful way of reconnecting to our environment."},{"time":791000,"text":"I've had the privilege of living by a meadow"},{"time":793000,"text":"for the last little while, and it is terribly engaging."},{"time":797000,"text":"And if we look at the history of lawns, it's actually rather tragic."},{"time":802000,"text":"It used to be, two, three hundred years ago,"},{"time":804000,"text":"that a lawn was a symbol of prestige,"},{"time":806000,"text":"and so it was only the very rich that could keep these green"},{"time":809000,"text":"actually, deserts: they're totally sterile."},{"time":812000,"text":"Americans spent, in 2001 -- 11 percent of all pesticide use was done on lawns."},{"time":817000,"text":"Five percent of our greenhouse gases are produced by mowing our lawns."}]},{"cues":[{"time":823000,"text":"And so it's incredible the amount of resources we've spent"},{"time":826000,"text":"keeping our lawns, which are these useless biosystems."},{"time":830000,"text":"And so we need to rethink this idea."},{"time":833000,"text":"In fact, you know, the White House"},{"time":835000,"text":"used to have sheep in front in order to help fund"},{"time":837000,"text":"the war effort in World War I, which probably is not a bad idea;"},{"time":840000,"text":"it wouldn't be a bad idea."},{"time":841000,"text":"I want to say this not because I'm opposed completely to mowing lawns."},{"time":844000,"text":"I think that there is perhaps some advantage to keeping lawns"},{"time":848000,"text":"at a limited scale, and I think we're encouraged to do that."},{"time":852000,"text":"But I also want to reinforce some of the ideas we've heard here,"},{"time":854000,"text":"because having a meadow or living by a meadow is transformational."},{"time":859000,"text":"That it is amazing that connection we can have with what's there."},{"time":863000,"text":"These milkweed plants have grown up in my meadow"},{"time":865000,"text":"over the last four years. Add to watch the different plants,"},{"time":869000,"text":"or insects, that come to these flowers, to watch that --"},{"time":873000,"text":"and we've heard about, you know, this relationship you can have with wine,"},{"time":876000,"text":"this companion you can have as it matures"},{"time":879000,"text":"and as it has these different fragrances."},{"time":881000,"text":"And this is a companion,"},{"time":883000,"text":"and this is a relationship that never dries up."},{"time":886000,"text":"You never run out of that companion as you drink this wine, too."},{"time":890000,"text":"And I encourage you to look at that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":893000,"text":"Now, not all of us have meadows,"},{"time":895000,"text":"or lawns that we can convert, and so you can always, of course,"},{"time":898000,"text":"grow a meadow in a pot."},{"time":900000,"text":"Bees apparently, can be the gateway to, you know, other things."},{"time":903000,"text":"So I'm not saying that you should plant a meadow of pot,"},{"time":907000,"text":"but a pot in a meadow."},{"time":910000,"text":"But you can also have this great community of city"},{"time":913000,"text":"or building-top beekeepers, these beekeepers that live --"},{"time":916000,"text":"This is in Paris where these beekeepers live."},{"time":919000,"text":"And everyone should open a beehive,"},{"time":921000,"text":"because it is the most amazing, incredible thing."},{"time":924000,"text":"And if we want to cure ourselves of NDD, or Nature Deficit Disorder,"},{"time":927000,"text":"I think this is a great way of doing it."},{"time":929000,"text":"Get a beehive and grow a meadow,"},{"time":931000,"text":"and watch that life come back into your life."},{"time":934000,"text":"And so with that, I think that what we can do, if we do this,"},{"time":938000,"text":"we can make sure that our future -- our more perfect future --"},{"time":941000,"text":"includes beekeepers and it includes bees and it includes those meadows."},{"time":946000,"text":"And that journey -- that journey of transformation that occurs"},{"time":949000,"text":"as you grow your meadow and as you keep your bees"},{"time":952000,"text":"or you watch those native bees there -- is an extremely exciting one."},{"time":956000,"text":"And I hope that you experience it"},{"time":957000,"text":"and I hope you tell me about it one day."},{"time":960000,"text":"So thank you very much for being here. \nThank you very much."}]}]}